Dimension reduction for MNIST dataset

Dense shallow network for classifying MNIST dataset

## Warning: package 'keras' was built under R version 3.4.3
library(keras)
use_condaenv("r-tensorflow",conda=YOUR.PATH.TO.CONDA)

Download data

Use the package quantmod to retrieve financial data:

chartSeries(TSM,type="line",theme=chartTheme("white"))

close <- as.matrix(Cl(TSM))
n <- dim(close)[1]

Reshape and rescale data

time_steps <- 1
data_dim <- 1
x_train <- array_reshape(close[1:(n-100-1)],c(n-100-1,time_steps,data_dim))
y_train <- close[2:(n-100)]
x_test <- array_reshape(close[(n-100):(n-1)],c(100,time_steps,data_dim)) 
y_test <- close[(n-100+1):n]

Define deep lstm model

model <- keras_model_sequential()
layer_lstm(model, units=20, activation='relu', input_shape=c(time_steps,data_dim))
layer_lstm(units=20, activation='relu')
## <keras.layers.recurrent.LSTM>
layer_lstm(units=20, activation='relu', return_state=TRUE)
## <keras.layers.recurrent.LSTM>
layer_dense(model,units=1,activation='linear')

Compile and fit the model

compile(model,loss="mean_squared_error",optimizer="nadam")
history <- fit(model,x_train,y_train,batch_size=100,epochs=100)
plot(history)

plot(y_test,predict(model,x_test))
abline(0,1)
